"Terminal Cancer Couloir" in the Ruby Mts, NV on March 9, 2021 was a rowdy experience! I was on the road in Park City, UT at 3:30am MT, boot-packing up the couloir by 6:30am PT, then skiing KT laps at @squawalpine CA at 2:30pm PT. The chute itself was dust on crust but still really fun. It's simply surreal being in such a tight, tall walled chute that goes for so long. The full ski is about 1,900'-vertical-feet! This was a day I won't soon forgot. 
Full Report in Link IN BIO ☣️
🧠 @miles_clark 
🎿 @scottfreeski @scottsportsusa 
👣 @intuitionliners 
🍺 @10barrelbrewing

Ever seen rime-ice this thick!? Dayum 😯🧊💪...
🌋 @mtruapehu NZ
🗓️ This week

"We've noted some concerns regarding our High Noon Express and we want to assure you, she's ok! The challenge we have had in getting the lift operational is de-icing. (These photos are from today, after yesterday's de-icing efforts!) 

While stunning, refreezing conditions since the storm have led to constant and repeated de-icing. De-icing on the Noon is so important as the lift has detachable chairs and the chairs won't attach if there are any obstructions, e.g. ice, on the cable. If the wheels (sheaves) are frozen, they can't spin and the cable can wear into the rubber, damaging it.

The de-icing process combined with general post storm clean up and work required to get other lifts operational, has meant we haven't got the Noon going as soon as we (and you) would have liked. 

Climbing the 12+ metre towers and swinging bats all day has been tiring, but Safety Services and Maintenance team members, qualified and trained to work at that height, have pitched in alongside our legendary de-icing & lifts team #wearetūroa.

Alongside de-icing, our first priority is to build the trails off the Noon before we look at building the trails down to the Nga Wai Heke. Four days ago we couldn't even get out west from the Noon! Whereas now we can get up high and west, and also have enough snow to get a look at the Nga Wai Heke after that. So as always, keep an eye on the reports for when the Noon and other lifts will open and really, #thankyourlocaldeicer, #thankyourlocalgroomer, #actuallythankyourlocaleveryone - as we assure you, they are all putting in the mahi." @mtruapehu

📸 : Raphael, Ren & Rosie Morrow
